        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p><span>A <em>horn of blasting</em> is a bright brass trumpet. It can be played as an instrument, granting a +2 item bonus to your Performance check.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Activate</strong> <span style=\"font-family: 'Pathfinder2eActions'; font-size: 1.8em; display: inline;\">A</span> Interact; <strong>Frequency</strong> once per round; <strong>Effect</strong> When you activate the horn by blowing into it with destructive intent, you create a blast note targeting one creature or object within 30 feet. The blast deals 3d6 sonic damage. (DC 28 basic Fortitude save).<br /></span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Activate</strong> <span style=\"font-family: 'Pathfinder2eActions'; font-size: 1.8em; display: inline;\">D</span> Interact; <strong>Frequency</strong> once per day; <strong>Effect</strong> You can blow even louder to create an intense blast wave in a 30-foot cone that deals 8d6 sonic damage. Each creature attempts a DC 28 Fortitude save with the following effects. <br /></span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature takes no damage.<br /><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.<br /><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and is deafened for 2d6 rounds.</span></p>"
